Text: Throughput Forecastwould like to schedule a meeting to discuss the components for modeling TW throughput The first date Kim Lindy Sean and I could make was Friday August th How does everyone elses schedule look for the morning of the th
Throughput Forecast Meeting Confitmation Cc reserved from for our meeting on Friday August th If you have not already marked your calendar please do

Variablesattached file contains a list of the variables we identified in our August th meeting I tried to break them down into smaller group just for organizational purposes The items under Prices and Temperatures should be easy to gather using the LIM database The items in the Other category may require more research What we have done in the past if we could not find the exact variable try and fine a proxy for it For example it may be difficult to find irrigation usage but less difficult to find precipitation in a region Since these two items would intuitively seem to have an inverse relationship it may be possible to use precipitation as a proxy for irrigation After we have begun to research the Other variables we may have to come back to you and discuss proxy variables so keep that in mind We added a column for use to keep track of the statues on each variable this is just for us to keep track of where we found the variable or why we did not pursue it Let me know if we have missed anything or you have subsequently thought of anything not on the list
